node.text:
National parks have captured our hearts. They honor our history and unite us as a nation. They’re the backdrops for some of our happiest moments. They help us discover who we are, and heal our minds, bodies and souls. National parks are our nation’s greatest love story, but over the years, their bridges, roads and visitor centers have become worn and many are now in disrepair. Our 400+ national parks have an $11.6 billion backlog in maintenance needs, and we’re working to #RebuildOurParks to ensure they remain as extraordinary as when we first fell in love with them. What’s your national park love story? 
Music by Borrtex "Ocean" (@borrtex).

node.text: Experience all that Haleakala National Park has to offer — from sandy beaches and lush forests to amazing sunrises and stunning waterfalls.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Department of the Interior in Vermilion Cliffs National Monument. May be an image of tree, nature and sky.

node.text:
Located on the Colorado Plateau in northern #Arizona, the @mypubliclands Vermilion Cliffs National Monument is a geologic treasure. Known more for its colorful stone waves, the secret to this monument is the pristine night skies. 

Photo by Lawrence Pallant (sharetheexperience.org). Photo description: A night sky filled with stars hangs over a plated rocky hill with a lone green pine tree in the middle. #usinterior #nightsky #perseids

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Department of the Interior in Channel Islands National Park. May be an image of nature.

node.text:
Welcome to another edition of Is It Real, Or Is It Fake? 

Once again, we’re your host Interior. 

The sea pickles at @channelIslandsnps, are tubes made up of a colony of fast-growing pelagic tunicates rather than a singular animal. Sea 🥒's. Real or Fake? 

Friends, the answer is REAL! Sea pickles or pyrosomes also serve as a food source for several kelp forest species such as sea stars, sea urchins, sea anemones, crabs, kelp bass, and opaleye. These amazing pickles can also emit a beautiful bright blue-green bioluminescence that can be seen at night. 

Photo of sea pickle in a kelp forest, by @nationalparkservice. Photo description: A long tube-like sea pickle floats through a kelp forest in the ocean. #usinterior #themoreyouknow

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Department of the Interior in Joshua Tree National Park. May be an image of sky, tree and nature.

node.text:
Happy Birthday to @joshuatreenps! 

Made a national monument on August 10th, 1936 and then designated a national park in 1994, this unique desert ecosystem is home to Dr. Seuss-like trees, epic night skies, and one of the most stunning landscapes in the state of #California. 

Photo of Joshua Tree sunset by Emily Hassell, @nationalparkservice. Photo description: Rows of Joshua trees stand tall in the desert as a pink and blue sunset sky glows behind them. #usinterior #happybirthday

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Department of the Interior in North Cascades National Park Service Complex. May be an image of lake and nature.

node.text:
Fun national park fact alert! 🚨

Visitors to @ncascadesnps in #Washington frequently ask the rangers, “Why is Diablo Lake that color?” 

During the summer, ice melt and erosion from the surrounding mountains, bring glacial flour into the lake. These fine rock particles refract the sunlight and turn the lake a dazzling turquoise. 

The color is most vibrant on sunny days in July, August, and September when seasonal glacial melt occurs. 

Photo by Alisha Clarke (sharetheexperience.org) A turquoise colored lake is surrounded by steep mountains on all sides. #usinterior #themoreyouknow

location.name: North Cascades National Park Service Complex

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Department of the Interior in Papahānaumokuākea Marine National Monument. May be an image of bird, body of water and nature.

node.text:
When your mom brings you to karaoke night at the local sea turtle hangout. 🎤🎶

At Papahānaumokuākea Marine National Monument in #Hawaii, an adult brown booby is using a Hawaiian green sea turtle (honu) as its own personal stage. Its young chick looks on (probably embarrassed) and the turtle doesn’t seem too bothered by the whole ordeal. 

Papahānaumokuākea not only has turtle stages, but it is also center stage to over 14 million seabirds and home to the threatened Hawaiian green sea turtle. This massive collection of coral islands, seamounts and shoals stretches across thousands of miles of Pacific Ocean and is one of the largest marine conservation areas in the world. 

Access to this special place is limited only to those conducting scientific research, cultural practices, restoration efforts, and other limited activities, so you could say that Papahānaumokuākea is literally FOR the birds. Because of the lack of human activity, Papahānaumokuākea can support an incredible diversity of fish, birds, mammals and marine life and remain a sanctuary for some of the most threatened and endangered species on the planet to live and thrive. 

Photo by Koa Matsuoka, @usfws. Photo description: An adult brown booby bird stands on the back of a sea turtle while a brown booby chick stands off to the side. A calm blue ocean is behind them. #usinterior #seaturtle

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Department of the Interior in Cape Hatteras National Seashore. May be an image of sky and nature.

node.text:
What better way to celebrate National Lighthouse Day than by showcasing the famous Bodie Island Light Station @capehatterasnps in #NorthCarolina? 

The light was electrified in 1932, phasing out the need for on-site keepers. Finally, all of the light station’s property, except the tower, was transferred to the National Park Service in 1953. 

The keepers' duplex has since undergone two historic restorations, the last having been completed in May 1992. The building now serves as a ranger office and visitor center for Cape Hatteras National Seashore. The most recent restoration of the lighthouse itself was completed in 2013. Still a functioning navigational aid, the tower is open for public tours.

Pic by James Jenkins (sharetheexperience.org). Photo description: A lighthouse stands tall underneath a starry night sky. #usinterior #nationallighthouseday

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Department of the Interior in Rocky Mountain National Park. May be an image of nature.

node.text:
Starting in June, the fields of #Colorado blue columbine decorate high elevations at @rockynps. 

A hike to Sky Pond begins from the Glacier Gorge Trailhead and rewards adventurers with striking views of jagged cliff faces that rise dramatically from the fields of wildflowers. 

To enter the park between May 28 and October 11 requires two things: a Timed Entry Permit or a reservation with a service, plus a Park Pass or Entrance Fee. 

Photo courtesy of Matthew Terral @matthewterral. Photo description: Jagged cliffs rise above Sky Pond, reflecting the rocks and the sky with the foreground decorated in columbine wildflowers. #usinterior #findyourpark

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Department of the Interior in Sleeping Bear Dunes National Lakeshore. May be an image of nature and lake.

node.text:
The night settles in with bird and frog song at the beautiful @sleepingbearnps in #Michigan. 

In addition to the open water of Lake Michigan and the inland lakes, there are dozens of small wetlands, bogs, and marshes ready to explore. Coastal beauty sweeps through the area and there are opportunities to fish, canoe, and take to the trail. Though named for the dunes, these areas reveal another side of the park, just as wild and stunning. 

Photo by Furguson, @nationalparkservice. Photo description:  Sunset colors reflect over a pond with lily pads. #usinterior #findyourpark

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Department of the Interior in Basin and Range National Monument. May be an image of sky and nature.

node.text:
The @mypubliclands Basin and Range National Monument in #Nevada is a vast and rugged landscape that redefines our notions of distance and space and where opportunities for solitude abound. 

About two hours north of Las Vegas, this newer 704,000-acre monument created in 2015, provides for all types of outdoor recreation, including climbing, hiking, bicycling, camping, hunting, OHV riding (except in the Worthington Mountains Wilderness) and more. 

Photo by Bob Wick, BLM. Photo description: A large stone arch is stretched out across a desert landscape. A moon can be seen through the window of the arch. #usinterior #TeamPublicLands

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Department of the Interior in Yellowstone National Park. May be an image of body of water and nature.

node.text:
Today marks the anniversary of the Great American Outdoors Act. 🥳 

This important law funds enhancements to our national parks and recreation areas, creates jobs, and helps fight climate change by preserving our public lands, outdoor spaces, and the wildlife that call them home. 

Photo of Yellowstone National Park by @nationalparkservice. Photo description: A steep narrow canyon with a fast moving river is causing mist to rise and reflect a rainbow. #usinterior #anniversary

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Department of the Interior in Petit Manan National Wildlife Refuge. May be an image of bird and nature.

node.text:
It was at that moment, the fish regretted its decision to get out of bed that morning. 🦅 

Scenes like this play out every day at the @usfws Maine Coastal Islands National Wildlife Refuge. The fish will sometimes escape, but the bald eagle is always the top predator in this version of hunter vs. hunted. 

Photo by Winston Shaw (sharetheexperience.org). Photo description: A bald eagle swoops down from the sky to scoop up a fish from the water. #usinterior #gofish

Aw! **Warm fuzzies instantly fill brain** 

These two sibling arctic foxes in #Alaska are playing together. For young foxes like these, rough-housing and play are essential for learning life skills. In the fall, the family will part ways, and the young will be ready to take on the tundra, thanks in part to play with their siblings. 

Video by Lisa Hupp, @usfws. Video description: two young foxes play. One pulls the tail of the other, and then the fox boops the nose of their sibling fox. #usinterior #wildlife
